title.narrative: Fourth Roads Rehabilitation and Maintenance Project

description.narrative: The Project Development Objective is to support the Government of Nicaragua's broad based economic growth and poverty reduction plan by relieving transportation bottlenecks that currently hinder economic growth and private sector investment. The specific objectives are to support economic growth by: (i) expanding and complementing the previous focus on trunk roads by improving a connecting network of secondary and rural roads ; (ii) helping ensure the sustainability of the road improvements, through strengthening of maintenance practices, and (iii) institution building and technical development in the Ministry of Transport and Infrastructure (MTI) and the Road Maintenance Fund (FOMAV).
